<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Total body length ranged between 15 and 49 mm. Tail 19-24% of body length. Hooks 4-11. Anterior teeth 2-4 and posterior teeth 2-9, respectively. Large and translucent body (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. A Flaccisagitta hexaptera (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; IN = intestine; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704199" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">15</figureCitation>
). Intestinal diverticula absent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. A Flaccisagitta hexaptera (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; IN = intestine; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704199" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">15B</figureCitation>
). Collarette absent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. A Flaccisagitta hexaptera (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; IN = intestine; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704199" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">15A</figureCitation>
). Eyes 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“D”">&quot;D&quot;</normalizedToken>
shaped with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“T”">&quot;T&quot;</normalizedToken>
shaped eye pigments (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. A Flaccisagitta hexaptera (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; IN = intestine; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704199" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">15B</figureCitation>
). Anterior fins short, beginning at middle of body between ventral ganglion and caudal septum, round-shaped and partially rayed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. A Flaccisagitta hexaptera (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; IN = intestine; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704199" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">15A, D</figureCitation>
). Posterior fins well-separated from anterior fins and partially rayed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. A Flaccisagitta hexaptera (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; IN = intestine; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704199" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">15A, E</figureCitation>
). Caudal fin roundish triangular-shaped and completely rayed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. A Flaccisagitta hexaptera (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; IN = intestine; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704199" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">15A, C</figureCitation>
). Seminal vesicles spherical with anterolateral edge opening (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. A Flaccisagitta hexaptera (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; IN = intestine; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704199" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">15C</figureCitation>
). Seminal vesicle touching or close to tail fin and well-separated from lateral fins (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. A Flaccisagitta hexaptera (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; IN = intestine; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704199" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">15C</figureCitation>
). Eggs reaching forward end of anterior fins. Corona ciliata beginning in front of eyes and reaching neck (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. A Flaccisagitta hexaptera (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; IN = intestine; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704199" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">15B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
